description:
ANN In-Depth host Sam Neves is joined by Justin Kim, pastor and Digital Evangelism Director of the Central California Conference, to discuss the innovative approach to digital evangelism being implemented in areas like San Francisco and Silicon Valley. Justin shares insights into the challenges and successes of reaching people online, particularly through the power of prayer. 

Episode highlights: 
-The unique strategies employed to reach people online.
-Utilization of prayer advertisements, personal follow-up, and the responsiveness of individuals to prayer requests. 
-The merging of traditional prayer methods with modern technology.
-How the Seventh-day Adventist Church is adapting to the digital age, reaching communities in need, and fostering meaningful connections through prayer and care.

This episode is for you if you aspire to spread the gospel online, if you lack an active local, in-person church, and especially if you have a heart for evangelism in any setting. 

The Seventh-day Adventist Church has been an established denomination since 1863. It is a global Christian family with over 21 million members who hold the Bible as the ultimate authority. We are believers who promise to help people understand the Bible to find freedom, healing, and hope in Jesus.
